1️⃣ Request kya hai SailPoint me?
Request basically ek object hai jo kisi bhi action ko represent karta hai jo user ya system ke taraf se IdentityIQ me perform karna hai.
Ye mostly account provisioning, access request, approval workflow me use hota hai.
Ye ek container hai jo store karta hai ki kya action perform karna hai, kis user pe, kis target system pe, aur kaun approve karega.
Request ke through hi approval items, workflows, notifications trigger hote hai.
Use case examples:-
Ek user ko Salesforce me access dena → ye ek Request create karega.
Manager ko approval bhejna → Request me ApprovalItem attach hoga.
Request complete hone ke baad workflow update hota hai aur account provisioning hota hai.

2️⃣ Request ke andar kya kya hota hai?
Main attributes:-
Attribute	     Description
id-------------Unique request ID
created--------Request kab create hua
modified-------Last update date
requester------Kaun ne request ki
target---------Kis account/resource pe action hoga
state----------Pending, Approved, Rejected, Cancelled
approvalItems--List of ApprovalItem (Manager approvals etc.)
comments-------Notes or comments added during workflow
workflowCase---Kaunse workflow me ye request hai
attributes-----Extra metadata, like priority, level, department
dueDate--------Kab tak complete hona chahiye
completedDate--Kab complete hua
result---------Final result/status of request
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Request States:-
Request ke state batate hai ki request ka current status kya hai. Common states ye hote hai:-
State	                          Description
Pending:----Request abhi pending hai, action ya approval ka wait hai
Approved:---Request approve ho chuka hai
Rejected:---Request reject ho chuka hai
Cancelled:--Request cancel kar diya gaya
InProgress:-Request abhi process ho raha hai
Completed:--Request successfully complete ho chuka hai
Failed:-----Request process fail ho gaya (errors ke karan)
OnHold:-----Request temporarily hold pe hai
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2️⃣ Request Results:-
Result bataata hai ki request ka final outcome kya hua. Ye mostly approval ke baad ya workflow execution ke baad set hota hai. Common results:-
Result	           Description
Success:--------Request successfully complete ho gaya
Failure:--------Request fail ho gaya
PartialSuccess:-Request ka kuch part succeed hua, kuch fail
Cancelled:------Request user/system ne cancel kar diya
Error:----------Request process me koi error aya
NoAction:-------Request perform nahi hua (skip ya ignore)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3️⃣ Request ke main methods:-
Note: Main methods jo mostly use hote hai, SailPoint ke SDK/Java API me.

🔹 Metadata (Audit):-
getCreated()
setCreated(Date date)
getModified()
setModified(Date date)

🔹 Approval Items:-
getApprovalItems()// List<ApprovalItem> return karta hai
setApprovalItems(List<ApprovalItem> items)
addApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item)
removeApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item)

🔹 Approval Actions:-
approve()                        // Request approve karta hai
reject()                         // Request reject karta hai
cancel()                         // Request cancel karta hai

🔹 Request Details:-
getRequester()                   // Request kisne kiya
setRequester(Identity requester)

getTarget()                      // Target account/resource
setTarget(Object target)

getState()                       // Pending, Approved, Rejected
setState(String state)

getAttributes()
setAttributes(Attributes attributes)
getAttribute(String name)
setAttribute(String name, Object value)

🔹 Workflow / Result:-
getWorkflowCase()                 // Workflow ka case object
setWorkflowCase(WorkflowCase case)

getResult()                       // Result object
setResult(Object result)
🔹 Comments:-
getComments()                     // List<Comment>
addComment(String comment)
🔹 Utility / Clone / XML:-
toXml()                            // Request XML me convert
fromXml(String xml)                // XML se Request load
clone()                            // Duplicate Request object
toMap()                            // Map representation
fromMap(Map map)                   // Map se populate
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getCreated() aur setCreated(Date date):-
Purpose:-
setCreated(Date date) → Request ka creation date set karta hai.
getCreated() → Request ka creation date return karta hai.
Ye mostly audit ke liye use hota hai, ki request kab create hua tha.

2️⃣ getModified() aur setModified(Date date):-
Purpose:-
setModified(Date date) → Request ka last modified date set karta hai.
getModified() → Request ka last modified date return karta hai.
Ye track karta hai ki request me last changes kab kiye gaye.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()Request ke andar approvalItems list hoti hai jo track karti hai ki kaunse approvals pending/complete hai.
2️⃣ Approval Item Methods:-
Method	                                                        Description
getApprovalItems():------------------------------Request me currently attached ApprovalItems list return karta hai
setApprovalItems(List<ApprovalItem> items):------Request ke approvalItems list ko set karta hai
addApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item):--------------Naya ApprovalItem request me add karta hai
removeApprovalItem(ApprovalItem item):-----------Specific ApprovalItem request se remove karta hai.

import java.util.List;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.ApprovalItem;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;

public class ApprovalExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Request object
        Request request = new Request();

        // ApprovalItem create karte hai
        ApprovalItem approval1 = new ApprovalItem();
        approval1.setApprover(new Identity("manager1"));
        approval1.setState("Pending");

        ApprovalItem approval2 = new ApprovalItem();
        approval2.setApprover(new Identity("manager2"));
        approval2.setState("Pending");

        // List me set karte hai
        List<ApprovalItem> approvalList = new ArrayList<>();
        approvalList.add(approval1);
        approvalList.add(approval2);

        // Request me set karte hai
        request.setApprovalItems(approvalList);

        // Get Approval Items
        System.out.println("Initial Approval Items:");
        for (ApprovalItem ai : request.getApprovalItems()) {
            System.out.println("Approver: " + ai.getApprover().getName() + ", State: " + ai.getState());
        }

        // Add new Approval Item
        ApprovalItem approval3 = new ApprovalItem();
        approval3.setApprover(new Identity("manager3"));
        approval3.setState("Pending");

        request.addApprovalItem(approval3);

        System.out.println("\nAfter Adding manager3:");
        for (ApprovalItem ai : request.getApprovalItems()) {
            System.out.println("Approver: " + ai.getApprover().getName() + ", State: " + ai.getState());
        }

        // Remove approval2
        request.removeApprovalItem(approval2);

        System.out.println("\nAfter Removing manager2:");
        for (ApprovalItem ai : request.getApprovalItems()) {
            System.out.println("Approver: " + ai.getApprover().getName() + ", State: " + ai.getState());
        }
    }
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()approve():--Request approve kar deta hai. Agar saare ApprovalItems approve ho gaye hai, Request state = Approved ho jata hai
()reject():---Request reject kar deta hai,agar aek bhi approvalItem reject hua toh. Request state = Rejected, workflow stop ho jata hai
()cancel():---Request ko user ya system cancel kar deta hai. State = Cancelled, pending approvals ignore ho jate hai.
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.ApprovalItem;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class RequestApprovalDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Request create
        Request request = new Request();

        // ApprovalItems create
        ApprovalItem a1 = new ApprovalItem();
        a1.setApprover(new Identity("manager1"));
        a1.setState("Pending");

        ApprovalItem a2 = new ApprovalItem();
        a2.setApprover(new Identity("manager2"));
        a2.setState("Pending");

        List<ApprovalItem> list = new ArrayList<>();
        list.add(a1);
        list.add(a2);

        request.setApprovalItems(list);

        // Managers approve one by one
        a1.setState("Approved");
        a2.setState("Approved");

        // Request approve method call
        request.approve(); // Request state = Approved

        System.out.println("Request state: " + request.getState());
    }
}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ getRequester() / setRequester(Identity requester):-
Purpose:-
Requester ye batata hai ki request kisne initiate ki.
Usually ye ek Identity object hota hai jo user ko represent karta hai.
setRequester() → request me requester assign karta hai
getRequester() → request me assigned requester ko read karta hai
Example:-

import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;

public class RequesterExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Identity object create (user)
        Identity user = new Identity("john.doe");

        // Request create
        Request request = new Request();

        // Requester set karte hai
        request.setRequester(user);

        // Requester get karte hai
        Identity requester = request.getRequester();
        System.out.println("Request initiated by: " + requester.getName());
    }
}
Output:-
Request initiated by: john.doe
✅ Ye basically track karta hai ki request kiske dwara create hua.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2️⃣ getTarget() / setTarget(Object target):-
Purpose:-
Target ye batata hai ki request kis resource/account pe perform hoga.
Ye Object type hota hai kyunki target ho sakta hai:-
Account (Account object)
Role (Role object)
Application (Application object)
setTarget() → request me target assign karta hai,
getTarget() → request ka target read karta hai.

import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.Account;

public class TargetExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Account object create (target resource)
        Account account = new Account();
        account.setName("Salesforce");

        // Request create
        Request request = new Request();

        // Target set karte hai
        request.setTarget(account);

        // Target get karte hai
        Account target = (Account) request.getTarget();
        System.out.println("Request target: " + target.getName());
    }
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Attributes

Ye methods Request ke extra metadata ko manage karte hai, jaise priority, department, level, ya koi bhi custom data.

import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.Attributes;

public class RequestAttributesExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Request request = new Request();

        // Attributes set karna
        Attributes attrs = new Attributes();
        attrs.put("priority", "High");
        attrs.put("level", "L2");

        request.setAttributes(attrs);

        // Single attribute set
        request.setAttribute("department", "IT");

        // Get all attributes
        Attributes allAttrs = request.getAttributes();
        System.out.println("All Attributes: " + allAttrs);

        // Get single attribute
        System.out.println("Priority: " + request.getAttribute("priority"));
        System.out.println("Department: " + request.getAttribute("department"));
    }
}

Output:

All Attributes: {priority=High, level=L2, department=IT}
Priority: High
Department: IT

✅ Attributes request ke custom data store karne ke liye use hote hai.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2️⃣ Workflow / Result:-
WorkflowCase → ye batata hai ki request kis workflow ka part hai
Result → ye batata hai ki request ka final outcome kya hua.
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.WorkflowCase;

public class RequestWorkflowExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Request request = new Request();

        // Workflow case set
        WorkflowCase workflowCase = new WorkflowCase();
        workflowCase.setName("ProvisioningWorkflow");
        request.setWorkflowCase(workflowCase);

        // Workflow case get
        System.out.println("Workflow Case: " + request.getWorkflowCase().getName());

        // Result set
        request.setResult("Success");
        System.out.println("Request Result: " + request.getResult());
    }
}
Output:-
Workflow Case: ProvisioningWorkflow
Request Result: Success
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3️⃣ Comments:-
Comments approval/reject notes ya audit trail ke liye use hote hai
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import java.util.List;

public class RequestCommentsExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Request request = new Request();

        // Add comments
        request.addComment("Approved by manager1");
        request.addComment("Provisioning started");

        // Get comments
        List<String> comments = request.getComments();
        System.out.println("Request Comments: " + comments);
    }
}
Output:-
Request Comments: [Approved by manager1, Provisioning started]
