4️⃣ Utility / Clone / XML / Map
Ye Request object ko serialize, duplicate ya map me convert karne ke liye use hote hai
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import java.util.Map;

public class RequestUtilityExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Request request = new Request();
        request.setResult("Success");

        // Clone
        Request cloned = request.clone();
        System.out.println("Cloned Result: " + cloned.getResult());

        // Convert to XML
        String xml = request.toXml();
        System.out.println("XML: " + xml);

        // Load from XML
        Request fromXml = Request.fromXml(xml);
        System.out.println("From XML Result: " + fromXml.getResult());

        // Convert to Map
        Map<String, Object> map = request.toMap();
        System.out.println("Map: " + map);

        // Load from Map
        Request fromMap = Request.fromMap(map);
        System.out.println("From Map Result: " + fromMap.getResult());
    }
}
Output (simulate):-
Cloned Result: Success
XML: <Request><Result>Success</Result></Request>
From XML Result: Success
Map: {Result=Success}
From Map Result: Success
✅ Ye methods mostly serialization, duplication, aur programmatic manipulation ke liye useful hai.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()equals(Object obj):--------Do Request objects ko compare karta hai (agar same request hai ya nahi)
()hashCode():----------------Request object ka hash code return karta hai (hash-based collections ke liye)
()toString():----------------Request object ka string representation return karta hai
()getErrorCount():-----------Request me kitni errors hui wo return karta hai (workflow/provisioning failures)
()setErrorCount(int):--------Error count manually set karne ke liye
()incrementErrorCount():-----Error count ko 1 se increment karta hai
()getWarningCount():---------Request me kitni warnings hai wo return karta hai
()setWarningCount(int):------Warning count set karne ke liye.
()getPartition(),setPartition(String):-----------Request ka workflow partition (distributed workflow ke liye)
()getHost(), setHost(String):--------------------Request ka execution host machine track karta hai
()getThreadName(), setThreadName(String):--------Request ka workflow execution thread track karta hai
()getRetryCount(), setRetryCount(int), incrementRetryCount():---------Request retry attempts ko track karta hai (failures ke case me).

1️⃣ Warning (getWarningCount / setWarningCount):-
Warning ka matlab hai request process ke dauran minor issues jo critical fail nahi hai, lekin attention require karte hai.
Example:-
User ka account already exist kar raha tha, par fir bhi request execute hui → warning generate ho sakti hai.
Workflow me koi optional step skip hua → warning.monitoring ke liye useful.

2️⃣ Partition (getPartition / setPartition):-
Partition ka matlab hai workflow ke execution ka segment / bucket.
Ye distributed workflows me use hota hai:-
Agar system me multiple workflow engines / threads run ho rahe hai, to Request ko partition assign kiya jata hai.
Partition decide karta hai ki kaunse workflow engine ya thread request ko execute karega.

()Partition rules:-
Partition XML me define ho sakta hai agar workflow configuration me set hai
Ya workflow engine automatic assign kar sakta hai load balancing ke liye
Partition ka value string hota hai, jaise "partition-1", "partition-2"
Example XML snippet (simulated):-
<Request>
    <Target>Salesforce</Target>
    <Requester>john.doe</Requester>
    <Partition>partition-1</Partition>
</Request>
Matlab: ye request partition-1 workflow engine/thread ko assign hogi
✅ Partition rules / XML configuration / engine logic pe depend karta hai.
Daily approval workflow me usually manually set nahi karna padta.

1️⃣ Retry Attempts (getRetryCount() / incrementRetryCount()):-
Retry attempts ka matlab:-
Kabhi kabhi request fail ho jati hai due to:-
Network issue
Target system down
Provisioning step fail ho gaya
Retry attempts track karte hai ki request ko kitni baar dobara execute karne ki koshish ki gayi.
--Workflow me ye kaise kaam karta hai:-
Request execute → fail ho gaya
Workflow engine retryCount check karta hai
Agar retryCount < maxRetries (system me configured) → fir se request execute
RetryCount increment hota hai → incrementRetryCount().
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Real Code Example – Partition ke sath Request
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointFactory;
import sailpoint.object.Request;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.object.Account;
import sailpoint.object.ApprovalItem;
import sailpoint.object.WorkflowCase;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class RequestPartitionExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // 1️⃣ Get SailPoint context
        SailPointContext context = SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext();

        // 2️⃣ Create Request
        Request request = new Request();

        // 3️⃣ Set Requester
        Identity requester = context.getObject(Identity.class, "john.doe");
        request.setRequester(requester);

        // 4️⃣ Set Target Account / Application
        Account targetAccount = context.getObject(Account.class, "salesforce:john.doe");
        request.setTarget(targetAccount);

        // 5️⃣ Set Partition (example: "partition-1")
        request.setPartition("partition-1");

        // 6️⃣ Add Approval Items
        ApprovalItem approval1 = new ApprovalItem();
        approval1.setApprover(context.getObject(Identity.class, "manager1"));
        approval1.setState("Pending");

        List<ApprovalItem> approvalItems = new ArrayList<>();
        approvalItems.add(approval1);
        request.setApprovalItems(approvalItems);

        // 7️⃣ Set Workflow Case
        WorkflowCase wfCase = new WorkflowCase();
        wfCase.setName("ProvisioningWorkflow");
        request.setWorkflowCase(wfCase);

        // 8️⃣ Save Request in SailPoint
        context.saveObject(request);

        // 9️⃣ Approve the Request (simulate)
        approval1.setState("Approved");  // Manager approved
        request.approve();               // Request state = Approved

        context.saveObject(request);

        // 10️⃣ Print details
        System.out.println("Request ID: " + request.getId());
        System.out.println("Requester: " + request.getRequester().getName());
        System.out.println("Target Account: " + ((Account) request.getTarget()).getName());
        System.out.println("Partition: " + request.getPartition());
        System.out.println("Request State: " + request.getState());
    }
}
🔹 Output (simulate)
Request ID: 12345
Requester: john.doe
Target Account: salesforce:john.doe
Partition: partition-1
Request State: Approved

🔹 Key Points:-
Partition set karne se workflow engine ko pata chalta hai ki kaunse node/thread me request execute hogi.
SailPointFactory.getCurrentContext() → ye SailPoint context provide karta hai, jisse objects (Identity, Account, Request) fetch/save karte hai.
ApprovalItems ke through approval process simulate kiya gaya.
request.approve() → workflow engine me state update + provisioning trigger.
